    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Up for sale is a 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2), a pure driver's specification featuring the 3.6L M96 flat-six engine and a tactile 6-speed manual transaxle. This naturally aspirated power plant delivers linear torque and a distinct horizontally-opposed acoustic profile. The chassis retains its surgical precision, utilizing a multi-link rear suspension geometry and MacPherson front struts that provide excellent lateral grip and communicative steering feedback. The braking system is comprised of four-piston aluminum monobloc calipers paired with cross-drilled, ventilated rotors for superior heat dissipation. This example has been maintained with an emphasis on mechanical integrity; the IMS bearing and rear main seal have been addressed to ensure the longevity of the reciprocating assembly. While the exterior shows minor road-going patina, the drivetrain remains tight with crisp synchros and a responsive throttle. This is an analog performance machine optimized for the enthusiast who values mechanical substance over showroom perfection.",
